modules.description: Calculates an index from a source blob using a hash table, then generates a list of Copy and Insert operations to represent differences between two blobs. It works with byte sequences and absolute offset-based data structures. This is used to implement efficient delta encoding similar to Git's internal diff mechanisms.

Generates a lightweight occurrence index from a bigstring using Rabin's fingerprint, enabling efficient comparison between two bigstrings. Produces a list of hunks representing the differences between a source and target bigstring. Supports reconstructing the target from the source and diff using a dedicated apply function.
